{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019PxNmqWqN83tTCteMimB6D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ES config uses:\n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-0\", \"es-1\", \"es-2\"]` - these are the node NAMES, not IDs\n- Transport TLS enabled with the same cert as HTTP\n- `verification_mode: certificate` (for transport TLS - certificates only, no hostname verification)\n\nWhen es-1 restarted and started fresh, it has the same node NAME \"es-1\" (because `NODE_NAME` comes from the pod name). The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` uses node names. But the cluster had already bootstrapped previously, so this setting is IGNORED after the cluster state is established.\nI'm realizing the core issue: emptyDir volumes are ephemeral and tied to the pod's lifecycle. When a pod terminates during the rolling restart, its emptyDir is wiped. So when es-2 was restarted, the old pod was terminated and its data lost, then a new es-2 pod came up fresh.\n\nThe new es-2 pod would have joined the existing cluster (es-0 and es-1 were still running) with a new ephemeral node ID, which is why it retained cluster membership. But then when es-1 was restarted, the remaining cluster lost quorum because es-1 was part of the master-eligible nodes.\n\nActually, the voting configuration is stored in the cluster state on es-0 and es-2, so they should have 2/3 quorum without es-1. But the logs show them saying \"have only discovered non-quorum\" because they see the new es-1 with a different node ID while still expecting the old es-1 to return. The cluster had three master-eligible nodes, and when es-2 restarted with a new ephemeral ID, the master accepted it into the cluster.\n\nWhen es-1 was terminated and then restarted, the remaining es-0 and es-2 should have maintained quorum with their stored voting configuration. The new es-1 instance starts fresh and tries to join, but the master (either es-0 or es-2) is stuck waiting for the original es-1 to rejoin rather than accepting the new one.\n\nLooking at es-0's election requirements, I can see the voting config lists three specific node IDs across two separate quorum conditions. The issue is that the voting configuration still references the old es-1's node ID, which no longer exists in the cluster. Set 2 has a problem: it only has one qualifying node (es-0) when it needs two, so the cluster can't achieve quorum.\n\nThe issue is that `POO5ryOxR-esWbKfWtzMAg` is missing—it was probably part of the cluster before but isn't running anymore. Rather than trying to fix this piecemeal, the cleanest approach is to delete all the Elasticsearch pods so they restart fresh together. Since `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is configured with the node names, they'll bootstrap a new cluster when they all come up at the same time.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1637,"cache_read_input_tokens":79315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1637},"output_tokens":41,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"719200ff-7cd2-49d6-aba3-40f90c5cb2aa","uuid":"58c39752-b58d-45e7-abcc-dae2af1276cc","request_id":"req_011CcMss9G5wEsW16P4kCbXE"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019PxNmqWqN83tTCteMimB6D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is stuck due to voting configuration mismatch. With emptyDir storage, the safest recovery is to delete all ES pods so they all start fresh simultaneously and bootstrap a new cluster using `cluster.initial_master_nodes`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1637,"cache_read_input_tokens":79315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1637},"output_tokens":41,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"719200ff-7cd2-49d6-aba3-40f90c5cb2aa","uuid":"a1e05e57-3954-4fbc-83af-8bc8cf295a16","request_id":"req_011CcMss9G5wEsW16P4kCbXE"}
